down significantly, but I do n't know that there is a resolution,'' he said. The Observer said the new <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> regulation reads: `` Firearms may be loaded when retained by police officers in the passenger cabin of an aircraft.'' The newspaper said the regulation was in a leaked copy of a `` restricted'' report on Flight 103 by the government's <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Ryde </PERSON>, a member of the committee, said armed police were not discussed when the committee held a crisis meeting in January, or at a regularly scheduled meeting in February. He said he had not seen the report.
