emicals.'' <PERSON> Rick </PERSON> <PERSON> Steiner </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alaska </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Advisory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Program </ORGANIZATION> said the beaches on which the herring spawn could be polluted. Fishermen said they have had two good years back to back, and some were spurred by that success to go into debt for new equipment this year. <PERSON> Ott </PERSON> said fishing is an economic mainstay in <PERSON> Cordova </PERSON>, more so than in <LOCATION> Valdez </LOCATION>, which also draws tourists and has the oil terminal. `` Half of <PERSON> Cordova </PERSON> is operating on credit,'' <PERSON> Ott </PERSON> said.
